The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 16 June is 42,887 (4,963.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 11 June, there were 277 new confirmed cases (32.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 04 June, there were 212 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 31% (65 extra cases).
